1. Problem Statement (Vietnam Context)

Vietnamese logistics suffers from structural seasonality + information lag.

Key pain points:

Demand spikes are predictable in pattern but unpredictable in timing & intensity

Formal data sources (customs, GSO, port stats) are slow, aggregated, backward-looking

Truck supply reacts late ‚Üí causes:

Price spikes

Empty backhauls

Driver shortages

Panic booking (‚Äúdesperation pricing‚Äù)

Vietnam-specific reality:

Real demand signals appear first on:

Facebook trucking groups

Zalo driver communities

TikTok livestreams (fruit harvests, flower runs, border congestion)

These signals are early, emotional, and spatial

‚û°Ô∏è Current systems are static
‚û°Ô∏è Vietnam requires dynamic, sentiment-aware logistics

2. Vision

Move from Static Logistics Planning ‚Üí Dynamic Sentiment Logistics

Use socio-spatial signals to anticipate freight demand before it hits the market.

3. Product Name
Socio-Spatial Freight Forecast (SSFF)

A real-time seasonality and desperation-index engine for Vietnamese trucking.

4. Core Concept (Standardized)

SSFF predicts where, when, and how intensely trucking demand will rise by combining:

Layer	What it captures
Social Signals	Real-time demand pressure
Spatial Data	Origin‚Äìdestination imbalance
Seasonal Patterns	Repeating Vietnamese cycles
Sentiment & Urgency	‚ÄúDesperation factor‚Äù
